					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">What if the default settings of monitors aren't the proper settings?  My LCD PC monitor's default settings puts contrast at 50 (out of 100) and brightness at 100.  If I put contrast at 100 and brightness at 0, it fixes the gamma problem somewhat, but it actually becomes extremely sensitive to viewing angle, so some pairs of colors (such as $0c and $02) still flip in luminance depending on if you're looking at the top or bottom of the screen.  My LCD HDTV's default settings sets brightness at around 33 out of 100 (there's no number) and contrast at around 67 out of 100, but there's no gamma problem.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

